attributes.full description: Mandaê joins logistics and technology to innovate the delivery industry with a fluid and uncomplicated service. Think "UPS without the trucks": Mandaê is reinventing parcel logistics through a digital platform that organizes the entirety of the parcel supply chain to deliver a seamless, high-quality and efficient parcel shipment service for SMBs in Brazil. The company's model is asset-light, working with players across each of the principal steps of the parcel supply chain: pickups, cross-docking, and last-mile transport. In a country where the national postal service is effectively the only shipping option for SMBs, Mandaê’s platform is the only one that allows them to use private transporters, helping SMBs save up to 35% on their shipping costs. Its mission is to “Connect Stories” through logistics. The company is well funded with backing from some of Latin America’s top investors, including Monashees, Qualcomm Ventures, Performa, Valor Capital, Hans Hickler (former CEO of DHL Express-USA) and others. Mandaê was selected to the 2015 Endeavor Startup Network, was winner of the ABComm Innovation in E-commerce Logistics Award in 2017, and winner of the São Paulo “Smart Cities” category of the 1776 Challenge Cup.

Arquivei for businesses connects to the Department of Finance, automatically downloads NFes issued for the CNPJ of companies, and stores them in XML and DANFE on Note Management Panel; keeps all invoices before the product arrives; and offers reports, filters, and intelligent search for any content of the notes. attributes.full description: Lean Survey conducts market research using thousands of crowdsourcing researchers to collect data from the offline world. Our mission is to democratize market research. The Lean Survey uses a mobile app, which can be installed on any mobile phone, for the collection of market research data. Our thousands of researchers are recruited through crowdsourcing and the entire training and auditing process is done remotely using innovative technology and methods. For the user, the Lean Survey is a smartphone app that pays money in exchange for you interviewing others. For businesses, the Lean Survey is a platform for engaging face-to-face or telephone market research in a streamlined and agile way. It is faster, cheaper and simpler than hiring a traditional institute with an equal / superior quality. With just under 3 years of company, the Lean Survey has already won clients such as Ambev, Kroton, Magazine Luiza and reached the mark of more than $ 1 million in revenue in 2017. Other than that, we raised 3 funding rounds with Angels and Seed Capital funds. We were recently invested by Canary (http://canary.vc/) and Harvard Angels

On the publishing side: - Fotolog (www.fotolog.com), bought by our shareholder Hi-Media SA: Hi-Midia is helping Fotolog grow in Latin America, where it already has more than 15 million Unique Visitors / month (source: ComScore) and is one of the leading community websites. - Blogorama (www.blogorama.com.br): a free blogging platform, organized around vertical categories (arts at www.arteblog.com.br, soccer at www.futblog.com.br, music at www.musicblog.com.br for example). Blogorama and its categories already reaches more than 1,5 million Unique Visitors in Brazil every month. - DaBlink: a web-based photo personalization tool. - AdoroCinema: the leading Brazilian website in the entertainment-movies category.  - new sites will be launched in Q1 2009. Hi-Midia main office is located in Rio de Janeiro, and a second office was opened in Sao Paulo in 2006. 60 people work in our Rio office, and 5 full-time in Sao Paulo. attributes.full description: Navegg is a Latin American company focused on online targeting that offers agencies, advertisers, publishers, websites, and blogs with Big Data, DMP, and analytics solutions. The company collects, processes, and organizes online users’ anonymous data to facilitate profile definition and clusterization in order to improve communication with the targeted audience, client relationship, and advertising campaigns.  It offers solutions for audience analysis, audience planning, and segmentation.Navegg collects navigation data on every website that has Navegg’s technology, a JavaScript tag. The data, which is anonymous, is analyzed and compared to other online users’ online behavior. These people are clustered according to mathematical and statistics’ methods which are based on market studies and research about consumer behavior and trends. It has over 100 million online users segmented according to their interests, purchase intention, online behavior, and social-demographics information.Navegg offers web analytic tools to facilitate data analysis and monitoring in online platforms. Navegg Analytics is a solution intended for blogs, institutional websites, and small ecommerce sites that have low traffic volume and only wish to analyze audience data. Navegg Ecommerce is a solution for small- and medium-sized ecommerce companies that have up to 1 million users and wish to understand their audience profile, abandonment percentage, and average ticket; and keep track of the attribution method and each campaign’s impact and ROI. The solution enables them to find out what other websites their audience visit and helps them do re-targeting, advertise on those websites, and personalize offers.Navegg is based in São Paulo, Brazil.

attributes.full description: Since 2013, Carenet has contributed to the digital transformation of the Brazilian health ecosystem through the integration and intelligent analysis of patient data with an emphasis on the use of Internet of Things (IoMT) connectivity platforms, interoperability and orchestration of patient telemetry data . Our hospital solution ORCHESTRA offers customers an innovative solution for their digital transformation in intensive care, with a focus on integrating data and information and remote monitoring of patients in a single management platform. The Carenet platform provides scalable and replicable technology for the construction of a Tele-ICU or a centralized clinical command center. ORCHESTRA as an integration system connects the hospital's hardware world with the software world in critical areas, such as the intensive care unit, the operating room and the emergency room. ORCHESTRA connects medical device data with a hospital's electronic health record system. This integration includes vital sign data from multiparametric monitors, such as heart rate, respiratory rate, blood pressure, temperature; or it can be device-specific, such as mechanical ventilator settings, infusion and nutrition pump flows, patient weights and positions in the case of automated beds. The technological and functional development of the ORCHESTRA platform that took place over the past two years has been evolutionary: First, we provide a simplified approach to the integration of medical devices connecting virtually any medical device to any hospital system. Then, we contextualize the clinical data, providing mobile and real-time information about the patient, which facilitates early intervention and allows for better clinical outcomes. Currently, we have taken intensive care in the ICU to the next level, with a layer of Tele-ICU functionality that provides online access to the patient's telemetry to specialists who are remotely monitoring the patient's clinical condition and are able to work and communicate with the local team. The ORCHESTRA tool is modular and compatible with any telemedicine solution on the market. Therefore, ORCHESTRA modules can be coupled to pre-existing telemedicine platforms in the institution. Our vision is to develop the tools that create real-time intelligence, insights, predictive analytics and healthcare for a growing new market for clinical surveillance.

Empreender no Brasil não é fácil, ainda mais quando o assunto ainda é polêmico, como no caso de moeda digital (criptomoedas) mas aos poucos estamos quebrando as barreiras de entrada e o fato do que está acontecendo no resto do mundo, como a China que já implantou e está testando a sua moeda digital, a empresa Visa que antes operava com carões de crédito e produtos financeiros, agora está patenteando o modelo de Blockchain para o Dólar Digital, whitepapers sendo escritos ao redor do mundo como o Euro Digital e de bancos Centrais utilizando moedas digitais (criptomoedas) e tokens, corroboram os dois anos que estamos trabalhando em nosso negócio, registrando pedidos de patentes e desenvolvendo aplicações para mostrar na prática o nosso negócio e o nosso propósito. Como temos expectativa de direito de exploração de alguns mercados, já estamos com a mão na massa para desenvolvermos aquilo que já fizemos as reivindicações de proteção. Temos em nosso roadmap o desenvolvimento de uma plataforma de pagamentos por aproximação e queremos incluir pagamentos utilizando nossa moeda digital (criptomoeda), tudo sendo validado e autenticado através da MIXVIP Blockchain que já foi desenvolvida. Estamos construindo todo um ecossistema, o que fica difícil explicar aqui e pode passar a sensação de falta de foco, o que na verdade é justamente o contrário, pois além de foco, temos definidas as etapas de desenvolvimento de cada produto e adotamos o conceito de customer development, quem manda no nosso negócio são os nossos usuários, tanto que, após o lançamento do nosso core business, que é o MIXVIP Bank e o MIXVIP Rewards, quem vai decidir quais os próximos produtos que vamos desenvolver serão os nossos usuários através de consenso utilizando um sistema de votos que será validado por um smart contract que vamos desenvolver utilizando a nossa blockchain que já está desenvolvida. Tudo com transparência e acessível a todos! Podemos rapidamente criar um dos nossos produtos com versões para Smart TVs e para smartphones, conforme eu demonstrei no vídeo sobre o MIXVIP On-Demand e está disponível no youtube. attributes.full description: Techtrials is at the crossroad of the information age of the Healthcare industry, combining years of experience in the pharmaceutical industry in clinical development environment and healthcare data science, applying big data, analytics and Artificial Intelligence.   We have a simple mission: “based on our unique mix of capabilities and proprietary technology, we are committed to continuously provide valuable clinical and RWE insights for the Health Industry which needs to act and take critical decisions in their daily operations.”   Techtrials Analytics delivers unique clinical and strategic insights to the Health industry across the value chain, offering unmatched intelligence and analytics data solutions.   We are an innovative, agile and dynamic trusted partner of healthcare stakeholders in their quest for cost effective and premium real world evidence (RWE) and actionable insights.   Our proprietary analytics platform benefits, TT Health Explorers is a BI & RWE Analytics platform, with more than 10 TB billion registries and unique proprietary technologies, that aggregate more than 195 million unique anonymized patients, 100% of available structured Public & Private Health data in Brazil. It maps all diseases by providing highly valuable insights that uniquely help the pharmaceutical, healthcare and government industries.   Our superior data solution portfolio, powerful analytics platform and core service offering generate cost-effective and cutting-edge healthcare analytics to help healthcare stakeholders act faster and decisively:   TT Disease Explorer – Understanding Epidemiology and Outcomes with RWE insights from Outpatient and Inpatient setting with data from Procedures, Treatments, Surgeries and much more; TT Onco Explorer – Understanding Epidemiology and Outcomes with RWE insights in Oncology from Outpatient and Inpatient setting with data from Procedures, Treatments, Surgeries and much more; TT Rare Disease Explorer – Understanding Epidemiology and Outcomes with RWE insights in Rare Diseases from Outpatient and Inpatient setting with data from Procedures, Treatments, Surgeries and much more; TT City Explorer – Public Health Strategic Management Tool combining RWD to understand the dynamics in each Brazilian municipality; TT Hospital Explorer – Public Health Strategic Hospital Management Tool combining RWD to understand the dynamics in each Brazilian Public Hospital; TT HCP Explorer – Healthcare Professionals Mapping Tool;

attributes.full description: We are a startup working with telemedicine to support medical decision, communication and care management for physical trauma patients and acute myocardial infarction.  The actual problem is that physical trauma patients are attended by non-specialized medical doctors in primary and secondary healthcare systems, or even inside the rescue ambulances, resulting in patient delayed delivery, without previous communication and lack of real-time data of trauma care chain. Using the TeleTrauma®, patient and trauma's data are imputed on the platform, with calculates the severity of seven different types of trauma, informing the best medical practice and the closest hospital with technical and human resources. By doing so, our client can deliver the patient to an adequate tertiary hospital communicating with trauma specialized medical doctors through telemedicine.  All data imputed in TeleTrauma® are displayed in a real-time dashboard panel for measurement of the efficiency of trauma care chain. In this case, the artificial intelligence has been applied to show the heat map of trauma for healthcare management efficacy.  Similarly, for acute myocardial infarction (AMI), we launched amIA®. This platform provides initial support for non-specialized MD who receives patients with chest pain. After imputing the patient data and a regular photography of electrocardiogram (EKG), the amIA's AI network calculates the probability of AMI and offers the initial support, adequate hospital recommendations and telemedicine with specialized MD. So far, amIA® has analyzed 15.000 EKG with 95% of accuracy.  In 2020 due to COVID-19 pandemia, w3.care has developed the TeleCOVID®. That is an operational telemedicine platform for people with respiratory symptoms after answering a triage, patients are divided in two groups: low and high risk. The second group is directly forwarded to a medical telemedicine support with MDs. Lower risk patients are given WHO recommendations automatically and ask to return in case of impairment of their clinical condition. All data collected is shown on real-time dashboard with epidemiological, operational and geolocation big data. Up to now, TeleCOVID® has more than 8k access on www.telecovid.com and 3.5K telemedicine support.

attributes.full description: Click Cash is a mobile App that simplifies the complicated and bureaucratic process of personal unsecured lending to individuals.  Available on Google Play Store for Android devices, the app uses BigData and Open Banking for a new approach to personal finance, enabling secure and reliable microcredit to financially underserved people, in addition to financial education to help them make the best use of the new credit options that are now opening for the general public.  Based out of São Paulo (Brazil), the Fintech startup was originally idealized by Estonian entrepreneurs that saw in Brazil and Latin America the opportunity to develop their solution. Key founders bring 15+ years of experience in online lending in Europe and were founders of Amarbank in Indonesia in 2014, which made IPO in January 2020.  In 2019 it was estimated 45M unbanked and 65M financially underserved, but active and connected people, in Brazil alone. A group that has a financial activity of more than U$154 billion / R$ 800 billion per year, and a huge unmet demand for microcredit.   Click Cash offers, in a 5 minutes process, from 100 USD to 1.000 USD loans to be paid back in up to 24 months. Flexible and adapted to the new digital economy, we work with other Fintechs and traditional banks alike, using the most advanced technologies in Data Analytics and Mobile Security, i.e: facial recognition and device behavioral analytics, as well as financial history, that enables us to run a full credit analysis in seconds creating personalized offers per user.  The Click Cash App was officially launched in March 2020, and by May 2021 had +460K downloads and reached Top 5 in finance Apps in Brazil, with 4+ stars rating in Google Play Store.

Midiacode's objective is to capture the physical world content into a very organized, accessible and shareable digital mobile one. The main usage of Midiacode is events, but it has been used also in education, smart cities and other markets where content delivery plays a key role. Analytics is one of the key benefits of Midiacode to customers. With the numbers from analytics, they can understand the real interest of people in the content of an event, for instance: which presentation was the best, the most desired? Which one was the most deleted one? The use of geofences and transmedia are also features that transform the experience of people with content. They can grab a presentation at the exact moment it is impacting them, and access it anyplace, anytime. Content is updated in the service, online, and automatically in the customers' mobile. They never get in doubt if the content they are accessing is the most updated one because it is. Customers can be notified by any change in the content they grabbed.

attributes.full description: Urbit was born with the objective of helping and empowering families in their decision-making on housing, businesses in their businesses, and public power and organized civil society in the discussion and formulation of public policies. To do this, URBIT is collecting in a single database any information that qualifies a geographical point, in its legal aspects (zoning, land use parameters and permissions), environmental, such as air quality and contaminated areas, services, flows of people and vehicles, urban safety, leisure, historical heritage, among many others. There is more than 100 information obtained after a simple mouse click. We expect our services to significantly impact the productivity and quality of our users' decisions.

attributes.full description: YLive is a biotechnology startup that develops solutions for animal nutrition and health using artificial intelligence. We offer a digital platform that analyzes genetically the animal gut microbiota and identifies microbiological “signatures” or biomarkers associated with health and performance. We are located at the largest technology-based incubator in Brazil, Cietec, at the University of São Paulo, and have a team trained to assist the development of animal husbandry and the rural producer. YLive is supported by the main financial agencies, universities and research institutes in Brazil.

attributes.full description: The SpecLab is a technology company specializing in the development of innovative analytical solutions using  Big Data  and  Artificial Intelligence. They offer solutions for the optimization of complex laboratory analytical processes in an efficient, economical and sustainable way, associating cognitive computing and spectral sensors to determine the nutritional, chemical, physical and biological properties of raw materials and products.
